Description: Limestone ostracon: On the recto a pair of large cartouches of Ramses X, and three smaller cartouches. On the verso scanty remains of eight lines of an unknown hieratic literary text.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Biban el-Muluk (Valley of the Kings - Thebes) (on internal evidence)
Curator's comments: Bibliography: S. Birch, 'Inscriptions in the Hieratic and Demotic Character from the Collections of the British Museum' (London, 1868), pl. II; K. Kitchen, 'Ramesside Inscription's VI (Oxford 1983), 699-700 (recto only).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393219) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393219)
